{
  "stem": "1400.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I took a shower when I got into Auschwitz, and that was the last shower I took for the next 11 months, or 10 and 1/2, 11 months.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But in Auschwitz, we had a barrack, a so-called wash barrack, where they had basins with running water.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we were able to wash our shirts and clothes and put on that and let it dry on us in the warmer days.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we weren't able to wash it in the winter months, because it would have-- we would have froze.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that-- the latrine was, again, another barrack with rows of cement pads with holes on them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And hundreds of people were sitting down at the same time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, a small incident happened with me in a latrine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I still-- I was wearing my glasses, and a little gypsy boy came by and grabbed my glasses where I-- where I was sitting.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that was the last time I had glasses in the camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I don't know why he needed it or what he did with it, but he grabbed my glasses from my face and run away with it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Never caught up with it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm shortsighted, but, you know, I can read close, and-- which we didn't.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't have chance.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But basically I can see even now but-- without glasses-- but I need my glasses.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Since age 6, I wear them like grown to my face.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It, it, it was still sore.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was still open sore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I put bandage on.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I, I got some rags to put on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I just managed with the sore foot.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And I went out to Landsberg with the sore foot.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it healed, you know, in December.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
